<item>
            <title>[LU-6970] llog_osd_put_cat_list() leaks thandle after failed declaration</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6970</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is in lustre-release/master as well. In llog_osd_put_cat_list() if dt_declare_record_write() fails then the thandle is never destroyed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        th = dt_trans_create(env, d);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (IS_ERR(th))
                GOTO(out, rc = PTR_ERR(th));

        lgi-&amp;gt;lgi_buf.lb_len = size;
        lgi-&amp;gt;lgi_buf.lb_buf = idarray;
        rc = dt_declare_record_write(env, o, &amp;amp;lgi-&amp;gt;lgi_buf, lgi-&amp;gt;lgi_off, th);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (rc)
                GOTO(out, rc);
        ...
out_trans:
        dt_trans_stop(env, d, th);
out:
        lu_object_put(env, &amp;amp;o-&amp;gt;do_lu);
        RETURN(rc);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
